          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The pyramid is centered in its local coordinate system, and the width and length of the pyramid are the dimensions of its rectangular base. For example, a pyramid of width ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "10.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " extends from ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-5.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "5.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " along the x-axis. The default width is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "1.0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". A width of zero or less creates an empty geometry.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can animate changes to this property’s value. See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.scenekit/documentation/SceneKit/animating-scenekit-content",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
